description:
Another year, another crazy birthday party.  Harlot was sleek.  It's sexy, dark, mysterious and cozy.  It's gorgeous.  The decor is moody and smooth, an modern version of a mansion from the dark ages.  It's not overly packed like a lot of the bigger bars/clubs, but enough people to get the mood in the right gear.  You'll still be bumpin and grinding.  

I had 2 tables there and the alcohol was flowing.  The ladies were sexy, and the music was perfect for the night.  Thank god I had reservations too, but apparently it was DJ Onemikes' bday party too, and he had waaaay too many people on his guestlist, which resulted in chaos at the door.  The doorman was an asshole that night, yelling at everyone "if you're not of the guestlist you're not getting in!" like some self-righteous bald guy, and pushing everyone away.  Loosen up dude, we're dropping some serious cash here, and you can't let a few more of my friends in for a bday party?

If you're setting up reservations, I recommend working with Christy.  She was a sweetheart that night.  So was out hostess, Genevieve.  Top notch service throughout the night.  There were some earlier confusions about the reservation process, but Christy immediately cleared everything up.  

The crowd belongs there, not like some other place with creepy dudes stalking out everyone.  Everyone's clean and fitting, and the girls were eye-catching.  I definitley recommend getting there by 10 if you're not on the guestlist, and hopefully with lots of girls.  Overall, the night resulted in:

- 10 Lapdances that I have no memories of;
- Falling over after one of the many patron shots, and catching myself by landing my hand in the icebucket, and struggling to get up;
- A lot of body shots, that I vaguely remember;
- Girl guy ratio of 5 to 1;
- Vodka cranberry stains all over my boxers the next day;
- Bruises ALL OVER;
- And finally, not getting out of bed until 4pm the next day.
